textBeforeTable: CodeStyle.Alpha Russian CAPTCHA Characters Windows Vista, 7, 2008 Server: Region and Language → Keyboards and Languages → Install/uninstall languages. Windows 2000, XP, 2003 Server: Regional and Language Options → Languages → Supplemental language support. If viewing these characters in your browser or generating them in Captcha images on your server fails, you can enable the required localization support for on both client and server machines using Control Panel: In ASP.NET and ASP Classic versions of BotDetect, generating localized Captcha images using these characters also requires supporting fonts on your server. Displaying these characters in your browser requires having fonts which support them installed on the client machine. This table on the left uses the actual Unicode characters drawn in localized Captcha images. Unicode Captcha Codes and Font Requirements The ru-RU Captcha locale uses the default Cyrillic character set, consisting of 25 characters. Russian Localized CAPTCHA Codes [back to top] ASP Classic applications use Redistribute\BotDetectSounds in the BotDetect installation folder by default. A custom folder can be specified in the BotDetect/CaptchaConfig.asp file. ASP.NET applications use Bin\BotDetectSounds by default. A custom folder can be specified in the <botDetect> configuration section. PHP applications always use lib/botdetect/Resources/Sounds. To use BotDetect sounds localized for the Russian Captcha Locale, you should also download the Russian Pronunciation Sound Package and deploy the .bdsp file to the BotDetect sounds folder your application
